⏺ Got it. Here's the synthesis of Eraser's actual grammar — turns out it's tighter and more elegant than I had it.

  Eraser's DSL — the real shape of it

  One unified grammar across all four diagram types. No type directive needed; the parser infers diagram kind from the constructs used. That's the genius of it.

  The core grammar (universal)

  // comments

  NodeName [attr: value, attr: value] {
    ChildNode [attrs]
    // nested children make this node a *group*
    // — group and node are the same primitive
  }

  Source > Target: optional label    // forward edge
  Source < Target                    // reverse
  Source <> Target                   // bidirectional

  That's it. Group is just a node with children. Edge directions reuse >, <, <>. Attributes in [ ]. Comments via //.

  Universal attribute keys

  ┌──────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │     Key      │                                                     Values                                                     │
  ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ icon         │ name from the catalog (300+ entries)                                                                           │
  ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ color        │ red, green, blue, yellow, purple, orange, grey, silver                                                         │
  ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ shape        │ oval, rectangle, diamond, rounded_rectangle, cylinder, hexagon, triangle, parallelogram, cloud, star, database │
  ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ style        │ dashed, dotted, bold, italic                                                                                   │
  ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ label / text │ display label distinct from the identifier                                                                     │
  ├──────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ colorMode    │ pastel, bold, light (deck-wide theming)                                                                        │
  └──────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Icon catalog (representative)

  - Generic (Lucide-style): user, users, home, folder, mail, key, calendar, clock, link, list, grid, repeat, send, zap, message-circle, bug, file-text
  - AWS: aws-lambda, aws-s3, aws-ec2, aws-rds, aws-api-gateway, aws-sqs, aws-sns, aws-cloudfront
  - GCP: gcp-pubsub, gcp-functions, gcp-storage, gcp-bigquery
  - Azure: azure-vm, azure-functions, azure-storage
  - K8s: k8s-control-plane, k8s-node, k8s-etcd, k8s-kubelet
  - SaaS: slack, kafka, databricks, snowflake, tensorflow, github

  Per-type constructs (still inside the same grammar)

  Sequence diagrams

  Same nodes + > arrows. Auto-creates a column on first reference. Adds block constructs:

  title User login

  User [icon: user]
  WebApp [icon: monitor]
  API [icon: server]

  User > WebApp: clicks login
  WebApp > API: POST /token

  alt [label: "If credentials valid"] {
    API > WebApp: 200 OK
    WebApp > User: redirect to /home
  } else [label: "If invalid"] {
    API > WebApp: 401
    WebApp > User: show error
  }

  loop [label: "Every 5 min"] {
    WebApp > API: refresh token
  }

  opt [label: "First login only"] {
    API > User: send welcome email
  }

  par {
    API > Analytics: log event
  } and {
    API > Cache: warm session
  }

  Block types: alt / else, opt, loop, par / and. All with optional [label: "..."].

  ER diagrams

  Entities are Name { ... } with one field per line:

  User {
    id Int pk
    email String unique
    createdAt DateTime
  }

  Booking {
    id Int pk
    userId Int
    createdAt DateTime
  }

  // foreign keys via dot notation
  Booking.userId > User.id

  Field types: Int, String, DateTime, Boolean, Json (extensible). Markers: pk, unique, fk. Relationships use the same > < <> operators (> = one-to-many parent-to-child).

  Cloud architecture

  Same node syntax. Icons + groups carry the weight:

  title Backend Architecture

  Web [icon: react, color: blue]

  AWS [icon: aws] {
    Lambda [icon: aws-lambda]
    Postgres [icon: aws-rds]
    Bucket [icon: aws-s3]
  }

  Web > Lambda: HTTPS
  Lambda > Postgres: query
  Lambda > Bucket: read assets

  Flowchart

  Same syntax. shape: attribute does the lifting:

  Start [shape: oval, icon: send] > Process [shape: rectangle, color: blue]
  Process > Decision [shape: diamond, icon: check-square]
  Decision > Success [color: green]: yes
  Decision > Retry [color: red]: no
  Retry > Process

